FBIS4-63492 "drsov099_f_94031" FBIS-SOV-94-099 Daily Report 20 May 1994 National Affairs UNA-UNSO Nationalists Call for Martial Law in Crimea UNA-UNSO Nationalists Call for Martial Law in Crimea LD2105113594 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2300 GMT 20 May 94 LD2105113594 Kiev UNIAR Ukrainian BFN [Text] Kiev, 20 May -- The Ukrainian National Assembly-Ukrainian National Self-Defense Organization [UNA-UNSO] people's deputies have submitted a draft resolution on settling the crisis situation in Crimea for consideration by the Supreme Council session. The UNA-UNSO resolution makes the following provision: 1. All Crimean administrative structures should be disbanded. 2. Emergency martial law should be introduced on the territory of Crimea. 3. All Crimean officials who are guilty of inflaming interethnic animosity, separatism and extremism should be arrested and held criminally responsible. 4. Additional Army and National Guard units should be brought into the territory of the peninsula to protect the civilian population from extremists. 5. Crimea's status as a republic should be annulled. 6. The performance of administrative functions in Crimea should be temporarily entrusted to the Ministry of Defense.
